[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Issue:** Lambda functions in a VPC need DNS resolution to reach the Neptune cluster endpoint (e.g., `my-cluster.cluster-xxxxx.us-east-1.neptune.amazonaws.com`). This requires the VPC to have DNS resolution and DNS hostnames enabled. This is a default VPC setting but can be disabled in custom VPCs. A Lambda that cannot resolve the Neptune endpoint DNS will fail with a connection timeout, which is a confusing error message.
